Here's the ViewModel using **CommunityToolkit.Mvvm** (recommended approach) and a matching XAML page with compiled bindings:

**ViewModel — `ProductDetailViewModel.cs`**

```csharp
using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.ComponentModel;
using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.Input;

namespace MyApp.ViewModels;

public partial class ProductDetailViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private string _name = string.Empty;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private decimal _price;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool _isAvailable;

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task LoadAsync()
    {
        // Replace with your actual data-fetching logic
        var product = await FetchProductAsync();

        Name        = product.Name;
        Price       = product.Price;
        IsAvailable = product.IsAvailable;
    }

    private async Task<(string Name, decimal Price, bool IsAvailable)> FetchProductAsync()
    {
        await Task.Delay(500); // simulate network call
        return ("Widget Pro", 29.99m, true);
    }
}
```

The source generator creates public properties (`Name`, `Price`, `IsAvailable`) with `PropertyChanged` notifications, plus a `LoadCommand` from `LoadAsync`.

**XAML page — `ProductDetailPage.xaml`**

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:MyApp.ViewModels"
             x:Class="MyApp.Views.ProductDetailPage"
             x:DataType="vm:ProductDetailViewModel"
             Title="Product Detail">

    <VerticalStackLayout Padding="16" Spacing="12">
        <Label Text="{Binding Name, TargetNullValue='Loading...'}"
               FontSize="24" />

        <Label Text="{Binding Price, StringFormat='Price: {0:C2}'}" />

        <Label Text="{Binding IsAvailable,
                      Converter={StaticResource BoolToTextConverter}}" />

        <Button Text="Load Product"
                Command="{Binding LoadCommand}" />

        <ActivityIndicator IsRunning="{Binding LoadCommand.IsRunning}"
                           IsVisible="{Binding LoadCommand.IsRunning}" />
    </VerticalStackLayout>
</ContentPage>
```

**Key points:**

- **`x:DataType`** on the page root enables compiled bindings (8–20× faster, AOT-safe).
- **`[ObservableProperty]`** generates the property + `PropertyChanged` raise — no boilerplate.
- **`[RelayCommand]`** generates `LoadCommand` with a built-in `IsRunning` property you can bind to an `ActivityIndicator`.
- **`StringFormat='Price: {0:C2}'`** formats the decimal as currency directly in XAML.
- Add `<WarningsAsErrors>XC0022;XC0025</WarningsAsErrors>` to your `.csproj` to catch binding mistakes at build time.

NuGet package needed: **`CommunityToolkit.Mvvm`** (≥ 8.2).
